 ran into this and it was driving me nuts. \r\n\r\nI was calling my setupChart function (which eventually calls moveViewToX) inside viewDidLoad and it would occationally do nothing (or for large values of X, seemingly greater than 50% of xMax... as well as more often on iPad than iPhones).\r\n\r\nMoving my setup function to viewDidLayoutSubviews fixed the problem in 100% of scenarios. This is on 3.2.2/Swift 5/iOS 12.2. \r\n\r\nI'm not sure this is a bug with Charts, but perhaps the documentation could be updated to warn devs to not make this (IMO) easy-to-do mistake.","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ChartsOrg/Charts/issues/comments/481317018/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"RamblinWreck77","id":22692130,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyNjkyMTMw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/22692130?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/RamblinWreck77","html_url":"https://github.com/RamblinWreck77","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RamblinWreck77/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RamblinWreck77/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RamblinWreck77/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RamblinWreck77/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RamblinWreck77/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RamblinWreck77/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RamblinWreck77/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RamblinWreck77/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RamblinWreck77/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}}]